[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    237[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m "The Technology: Grounded Generation for Structured Persuasion" section, "The key architectural principle: the model is a prose composer, not a fact source."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    238[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m This line is excellent. But elsewhere in the same section ("The LLM call itself is almost an afterthought" at the end of the General Architecture Pattern discussion) the metaphor shifts slightly. The "prose composer" framing is the one the reader should carry away; "afterthought" is less precise and slightly deflates the architectural core. Very minor.[K
